com.microsoft.azure.datalake.store

Class OperationResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.microsoft.azure.datalake.store.OperationResponse

  • public class OperationResponse
extends Object
    information about a response from a server call. This class is a container for all the information from making a server call.

      • successful

        public boolean successful
        whether the request was successful. Callers should always check for success before using any return value from any of the calls.

        public String opCode
        The WebHDFS opCode of the remote operation

      • httpResponseCode

        public int httpResponseCode
        the HTTP response code from the call

      • httpResponseMessage

        public String httpResponseMessage
        the message that came with the HTTP response

      • responseStream

        public InputStream responseStream
        for methods that return data from server, this field contains the ADLFileInputStream. null for methods that return no data in the HTTP body.

      • requestId

        public String requestId
        the server request ID.

      • numRetries

        public int numRetries
        the number of retries attempted before returning from the call

      • lastCallLatency

        public long lastCallLatency
        the latency of the last try, in milliseconds

      • tokenAcquisitionLatency

        public long tokenAcquisitionLatency
        time taken to get the token for this request, in nanoseconds. Should mostly be small.

      • responseContentLength

        public long responseContentLength
        Content-Length of the returned HTTP body (if return was not chunked). Callers should look at both this and responseChunked values to determine whether any data was returned by server.

      • responseChunked

        public boolean responseChunked
        indicates whether HTTP body used chunked for Transfer-Encoding of the response

      • remoteExceptionName

        public String remoteExceptionName
        the exception name as reported by the server, if the call failed on server

      • remoteExceptionMessage

        public String remoteExceptionMessage
        the exception message as reported by the server, if the call failed on server

      • remoteExceptionJavaClassName

        public String remoteExceptionJavaClassName
        the exception's Java Class Name as reported by the server, if the call failed on server This is there for WebHDFS compatibility.

      • ex

        public Exception ex
        exceptions encountered when processing the request or response

      • message

        public String message
        error message, used for errors that originate within the SDK

      • exceptionHistory

        public String exceptionHistory
        Comma-separated list of exceptions encountered but not thrown by this call. This may happen because of retries.
